# ============================================================================
# Notes
# ============================================================================
# This .gitignore is comprehensive for a personal ML/DL research project
# 
# Customize based on needs:
# - Uncomment sections as needed
# - Add project-specific patterns
# - Use ! to whitelist specific files
#
# Best practices:
# - Keep model weights out of git (use Git LFS or external storage)
# - Keep large datasets out of git (use DVC or cloud storage)
# - Keep API keys and secrets out of git (use environment variables)
# - Keep generated files out of git (can be regenerated)
# - Keep IDE-specific files out of shared repo
#
# For large files that must be tracked, consider:
# - Git LFS: https://git-lfs.github.com/
# - DVC: https://dvc.org/
#
# Verify what's ignored:
#   git status --ignored
#   git check-ignore -v <file>
# ============================================================================
